&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Communications, Public Relations, Journalism, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3+ years of relevant experience in a corporate communications setting, PR agency, or media/journalism industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive content creation and writing background, journalism experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid grasp of integrated marketing and communication strategies, with hands-on experience in digital channels (e.g., social media, content platforms, PR distribution networks) and offline channels (e.g., events, exhibitions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the media landscape, established network of overseas media is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative problem-solver with strong communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated and customer-centric&lt;/li&gt;
